VS Code Shortcuts Cheat Sheet for Smart Coders

General Shortcuts

Ctrl + P → Quick Open (Search files)

Ctrl + Shift + P → Command Palette

Ctrl + , → Open Settings

Ctrl + B → Toggle Sidebar

Ctrl + J → Toggle Terminal

Ctrl + Shift + N → Open New Window

Ctrl + W → Close Current Tab

Editing Shortcuts

Alt + Up/Down → Move Line Up/Down

Shift + Alt + Up/Down → Duplicate Line

Ctrl + D → Select Next Occurrence

Ctrl + Shift + L → Select All Occurrences

Ctrl + X → Cut Entire Line

Ctrl + / → Toggle Comment

Ctrl + ] / [` → Indent/Outdent

Ctrl + Enter → Insert Line Below

Ctrl + Shift + Enter → Insert Line Above

Shift + Alt + Left/Right → Shrink/Expand Selection

Navigation & Multi-Cursor

Ctrl + Tab → Switch Between Open Files

Ctrl + Shift + T → Reopen Closed Tab

Ctrl + K, Ctrl + O → Open Folder

Ctrl + Alt + Up/Down → Add Multi-Cursor

*Ctrl + Shift + * → Jump to Matching Bracket

Ctrl + M → Toggle Tab Moves Focus

Refactoring & Debugging

F2 → Rename Symbol

Ctrl + Shift + F → Global Search

Ctrl + H → Replace

Ctrl + Shift + H → Global Replace

Ctrl + . → Quick Fix & Refactor

F5 → Start Debugging

F9 → Toggle Breakpoint

Terminal & Git

Ctrl + ` → Toggle Integrated Terminal

Ctrl + Shift + C → Open New Terminal

Ctrl + Shift + G → Open Source Control (Git)

Ctrl + K + U → Stage All Changes

Ctrl + K + R → Discard Changes

Extensions & Productivity

Ctrl + Shift + X → Open Extensions

Ctrl + K, Ctrl + S → Open Keyboard Shortcuts

Ctrl + K, Ctrl + 0 → Collapse All Folders in Explorer

